The paper focuses on designing a human-computer interface for measuring human decision-making under risk, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of fuzzy-set theory and the consideration of human heuristics and biases suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of computational engineering (cs.CE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
